INSERT INTO `forum_replies` (`id`, `post`, `date`, `last_modified`, `thread_id`, `replied_id`, `replier_id`, `hidden`) VALUES
(1, '<p><span class="photo"><img class="photo_img img" title="photo1" src="https://scontent-sit4-1.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/66612_10200658230921275_135306612_n.jpg?_nc_eui2=v1%3AAeHx7y3y5kDNHdeWbtq1OYc4leJ3JLdr3oKIfgE0pRRjC4_fftDNfneX_Bkckc42dS-FO19tGyibki8wb3R4Yb1SmMgOP64nFdQ-43Geu9yvYQ&amp;oh=e318cb8de18913323c9ac36547169c78&amp;oe=5917ED5F" alt="photo1" /><span class="caption">photo1</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.I have surprisingly noticed that all major parties are using &ndash;some cases abusing the religion for their own benefit. What Awami league, What BNP or what Jamaat Islam &ndash;all are somewhat using it to gain popularity .</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2. American voter mainly concern about the economy. The health of economy is directly linked with healthcare, employment, business growth etc.So, when George H. W. Bush up for re-election, Bill Clinton focused on three slogans:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Change vs. more of the same</li>\r\n<li>The economy, stupid</li>\r\n<li>Don&#39;t forget health care.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In a democratic and developing country like Bangladesh, the economy should be the first and foremost important matter.</p>\r\n<p>However, what we can see now is that they have been using the religion as a election card for a such a long time that total voter polarized in major three groups.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>3. Bangladesh Jamaat-e-Islami (BJI) is the largest Islamic party in Bangladesh. They are so focused on sharia law and god that the people often forget their economy agenda. Their voters are mainly the religious people &ndash;more specifically those people who believe that the sharia should be only source of law. This group-however-believe that politics is the way to go to power. The BJI vote bank are mainly moderate practicing Muslim, and some hardcore religious people -but not too hardliner as they don&rsquo;t believe in democracy and &nbsp;tends to take arms in order to come to the power(such as abdur rahman and bangle bhai).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In a simple word ,we can say that the more people become practicing Muslim ,the more voter they gain.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;4.The&nbsp;Bangladesh Nationalist Party or BNP is one of the largest party in Bangladesh. Their voter are mainly the moderate Muslim who are somewhat concern about Islam.If we name it by its characteristics, It should be called &ldquo;Bangladesh Muslim Nationalist Party&rdquo; as non-Muslim rarely vote for this party.It mainly consists of both practicing and non-practicing muslim.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>So, the BNP wants more people become less practicing Muslim (not too less as they could be non-concern about religion) &ndash;not too practicing as it could change their voting pattern.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>5. The&nbsp;Bangladesh Awami League is one of the largest party in Bangladesh. Though, It&rsquo;s a secularist-capitalist party,It collaborates with communist parties. Awami league voters are mainly non-muslim which consist about 20% (e.g. Hindus, Christian, Buddhist, aboriginal tribal people, atheist etc), and non-practicing Muslim and practicing muslim who are not concern about religion in political arena.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>So, the more people become atheist, non practicing Muslim and practicing but not concern about religion much, the more they get benefited.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>6.Every party does whatever&nbsp; it takes to keep and enhance its Vote bank. Hence, BIJ will always try to tell the people that the Islam is the only way, BNP will always give soft support to Islam and Awami league will always try to keep people away from Islam.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>7. When our political discussion should be focused on economical development, health care ,job creation, development of country&rsquo;s&nbsp; communication system ,freedom of speech, human right, print and electronic media freedom, and poverty&nbsp; elevation, we are divided into many groups based on religion.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dated : Fabruary 18,2013.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Kashimpur,Gazipur,Bangladesh.</p>', '2017-01-31 03:47:28', '2017-01-31 03:47:28', 1, 0, 1, 0);
